1
00:00:01,319 --> 00:00:02,920
There was a TV screen

2
00:00:04,033 --> 00:00:08,583
They showed the executions they carried out, and their attacks

3
00:00:09,065 --> 00:00:10,388
And the killings they carried out

4
00:00:10,413 --> 00:00:13,479
Yes, of course there was a screen in the prison

5
00:00:15,486 --> 00:00:18,790
But honestly, I didn’t look at it

6
00:00:19,116 --> 00:00:21,116
Because I can’t bear to see a Muslim killed

7
00:00:22,298 --> 00:00:26,680
In fact, I can’t bear that for any human being, not just a Muslim

8
00:00:29,083 --> 00:00:30,580
This doesn’t need explaining

9
00:00:31,375 --> 00:00:34,313
When you see them killing someone

10
00:00:34,338 --> 00:00:36,249
It’s hard to look at it

11
00:00:37,493 --> 00:00:38,893
But the people who liked them

12
00:00:38,917 --> 00:00:41,665
They even put up screens in the streets

13
00:00:42,583 --> 00:00:46,021
There were screens in the middle of the streets, wherever you went

14
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:51,980
They would play them, and I don’t know how—maybe with discs

15
00:00:52,480 --> 00:00:56,004
They broadcast the videos they filmed on those screens

16
00:00:56,486 --> 00:00:57,709
And they showed them in the streets

17
00:00:57,736 --> 00:00:59,783
A lot of people watched them

18
00:01:00,181 --> 00:01:01,868
And some of them were happy with what they saw

19
00:01:03,191 --> 00:01:06,698
I mean, from watching people when we walked around the market

20
00:01:07,346 --> 00:01:10,669
I saw some of them watching, and some of them were happy

21
00:01:12,203 --> 00:01:14,433
Meaning they were their supporters

22
00:01:17,416 --> 00:01:20,830
Interviewer: Was the screen in the same room where you sat?

23
00:01:23,417 --> 00:01:25,278
And did they show anything else?

24
00:01:25,298 --> 00:01:29,178
Or did they only show executions, ISIS videos, and hand amputations?

25
00:01:29,655 --> 00:01:33,258
And how did you feel when they showed those videos?

26
00:01:33,971 --> 00:01:38,751
It was in the same room where we were imprisoned

27
00:01:40,530 --> 00:01:43,466
Up above, there was a screen in the room itself

28
00:01:44,758 --> 00:01:46,231
They showed only their ISIS videos

29
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,086
They didn’t show anything else

30
00:01:50,111 --> 00:01:53,951
Only killing, beheading, and their attacks

31
00:01:55,978 --> 00:01:57,185
That’s what they showed

32
00:02:00,875 --> 00:02:04,308
I mean, they didn’t show an Indian movie

33
00:02:04,368 --> 00:02:07,181
Or an Arabic movie, for example, for you to watch

34
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:09,050
No, only their ISIS videos were shown

35
00:02:11,438 --> 00:02:13,491
Interviewer: Could you write on the wall?

36
00:02:13,516 --> 00:02:17,035
I mean, did you see anyone else, or did you write a note on the wall?

37
00:02:17,831 --> 00:02:19,031
No, that was forbidden

38
00:02:21,224 --> 00:02:22,424
It was forbidden

39
00:02:24,572 --> 00:02:31,056
Imagine that from the toilet window

40
00:02:32,123 --> 00:02:36,579
I could see the roof of my house

41
00:02:37,833 --> 00:02:41,820
Meaning when I entered the toilet to relieve myself

42
00:02:42,705 --> 00:02:45,738
I would look toward my house to reassure myself about it

43
00:02:47,608 --> 00:02:50,261
I had little girls who sometimes played on the roof

44
00:02:50,275 --> 00:02:51,693
So I might see them

45
00:02:53,667 --> 00:02:56,491
Because my house was close, I might see them

46
00:02:59,917 --> 00:03:05,066
Interviewer: Did you learn who the jailers were who brought you the food?

47
00:03:05,292 --> 00:03:08,033
Or the ones who gave you instructions, for example

48
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:13,015
And what were their names? Didn’t you know who the jailers were?

49
00:03:13,871 --> 00:03:16,656
Who were they? Do you mean ISIS members?

50
00:03:17,461 --> 00:03:21,143
No, we didn’t know any of them

51
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,161
They were all strangers

52
00:03:25,792 --> 00:03:31,428
I mean their looks were unfamiliar to the area inside Mosul

53
00:03:32,344 --> 00:03:34,487
There wasn’t anyone from inside Mosul

54
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:37,625
From this entire Old City area

55
00:03:37,952 --> 00:03:40,021
Only ten from there were with ISIS

56
00:03:41,290 --> 00:03:43,359
There were many of them from other areas

57
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:47,900
But here, honestly, we didn’t have that

58
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,600
There were only a few ISIS members who joined them

59
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:52,800
I mean very, very few

60
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,300
Just a few people, you could count them on your fingers

61
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,800
Because people here didn’t accept that
